Former Secretary of State Lawrence Eagleburger, a distinguished diplomat and public servant, has passed away. He dedicated his life to serving the nation, first in the Army and then as a foreign service officer and statesman. Eagleburger played a crucial role in navigating the fall of the Berlin Wall and the end of the Cold War as Deputy Secretary and later Secretary of State under President George H. W. Bush. The nation is grateful for his lifetime of service, and condolences are extended to his family, particularly his three sons.